South African Corn Falls, Tracking Decline in U.S. Benchmark

-- B y   N i c k y   S m i t h
-- 
2011-03-08T10:20:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/south-african-corn-falls-tracking-decline-in-u-s-benchmark.html
Corn prices fell in  South Africa ,
tracking a decline in  Chicago .  White corn for July delivery, the most active contract on
the South African Futures Exchange, dropped 20 rand, or 1.2
percent, to 1,669 rand ($242) a metric ton at the 12 p.m. close
in Johannesburg. Meal made from the grain is the countryâ€™s
staple food.  Corn futures for May delivery fell 3.75 cents, or 0.5
percent, to $7.1325 a bushel on the Chicago Board of Trade in
electronic trading today, having retreated 1.4 percent
yesterday.  In South Africa, yellow corn for July delivery declined 17
rand, or almost 1 percent, to 1,705 rand a ton. The country
mainly uses the grain as  animal feed .  Wheat for May delivery fell 62 rand, or 2 percent, to 3,110
rand a ton.  Gains or losses for the most active contracts of three
additional crops today were as follows. All prices are in rand
